[{"id":"VR871955","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What is the distance between the central bright band and the next bright band in Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>2</mn> </math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR871955_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, students shine a beam of monochromatic light of frequency <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"f\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>f</mi></math></span></span> on a pair of slits that are separated by a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>. The slits are a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span> from a screen, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L is much greater than d\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"L is much greater than d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi><mo>â‰«</mo><mi>d</mi></math></span></span>. An interference pattern is formed on the screen, and the distance between the central bright band and the next bright band is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y sub 1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"y sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the students then submerge the entire apparatus (light source, slits, and screen) in a clear fluid with an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"n\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n is greater than 1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"n is greater than 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, while maintaining the original distances <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>d</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"L\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"L\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>L</mi></math></span></span>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a pair of slits between a light source and a screen. The slits are separated by a distance d. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR871955.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator y sub 1, and denominator n\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator y sub 1, and denominator n\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y sub 1\"><math alttext=\"y sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n y sub 1\"><math alttext=\"n y sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n squared, times y sub 1\"><math alttext=\"n squared, times y sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msub><mi>y</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]